Commentary: OUT! LBW! Gus Atkinson gets his second now! This is a huge wicket for England as Holder could have been a threat after his good knock in the first inning. This is on a good length and around middle, shaping in sharply and at a good pace, Jason Holder gets stuck in his crease and tries to work it away but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There is big shout for LBW, and up goes the finger. Holder takes the review and only height can save him here. UltraEdge confirms no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates that it is just clipping the leg pole. Holder is disappointed but he has to walk as the umpire's call goes against him here. West Indies lose half their side now!
